'''Mitchell Hanson''' (born [[February 9]] [[1988]] in [[Derby]], [[England]]) is an [[English people|English]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]], playing for [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] in the [[Football League Championship|Championship]]. His preferred position is at either right back or in central defence.

==Career==
He had extensive reserve team experience and made his debut for the reserve team whilst a schoolboy. Hanson's first taste of first team at Derby was appearing as an unused substitute in the 5-0 defeat away to [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] in April 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/4842672.stm|title=Reading 5-0 Derby |author=|publisher=BBC|date=[[2006-04-01]]|accessdate=2008-11-05}}</ref> Hanson, who graduated through the academy, signed his first professional contract with Derby in June 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/d/derby_county/6257300.stm|title=Teenage pair sign Derby contracts |author=|publisher=BBC|date=[[2008-06-30]]|accessdate=2008-11-05}}</ref> After struggling to break into [[Paul Jewell|Paul Jewell's]] first team, Hanson joined [[Football League One|League One]] strugglers [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] on a season long loan, despite struggling with a calf injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/7318555.stm|title=Vale sign Derby youngster Hanson|author=|publisher=BBC|date=[[2008-03-28]]|accessdate=2008-11-05}}</ref> He returned to Derby in April 2008, without making an appearance for ''The Valiants''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football.co.uk/port_vale/seven_more_players_leave_vale_263971.shtml|title=Seven more players leave Vale |author=|publisher=football.co.uk|date=[[2008-04-29]]|accessdate=2008-11-05}}</ref> He made his first team debut for Derby as an 89th minute substitute in a 4-1 victory over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 4 November 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/league_cup/7697249.stm|title=Brighton 1-4 Derby |author=|publisher=BBC|date=[[2008-11-04]]|accessdate=2008-11-05}}</ref>

==International Career==
Hanson has played for England at Under-18 level, showing his versitility by adapting to a holding midfielder role rather than his preferred position in defence.

